00:36.780 --> 00:38.460
And here are your hosts.

00:42.960 --> 00:50.260
This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. Here's Anthony as the author of over 30
science fiction and fantasy novels. His science fiction novels include Thone,

00:50.540 --> 00:58.420
Macroscope, and the Omnivore series. Anthony's fantasy novels include Hassan and
the well-known Xanth series. He's also written what he calls science fantasy.

00:58.680 --> 01:06.100
The best examples of this genre are his cluster novels and the associated three
-volume tarot novel. Since Anthony writes both science fiction and fantasy, we

01:06.100 --> 01:15.600
ask him which one he prefers to write. For the challenge, for the sheer joy of
getting in and tackling a difficult problem and surmounting it, science fiction

01:15.600 --> 01:31.260
is better. But if I need money, it's fantasy. I make my money on fantasy, and
it's very easy to do. So that it depends on what I really want. If I want to do

01:31.260 --> 01:41.840
something that I will feel will live after me and really be worth my effort,
then it is science fiction. But right now I would say, oh, about three-quarters

01:41.840 --> 01:51.080
of my money is being made in a fantasy. So that it is a certain pleasure to be
able to do something like that and just be richly rewarded for it. Not so much

01:51.080 --> 02:01.800
intellectually, but I can't just ignore the financial aspect. It's nice to be
paid well as well. But once he starts writing in either genre, Anthony admits he

02:01.800 --> 02:16.600
enjoys it. Actually, I do enjoy each when I get into it. Whatever genre or
whatever project I get into, I do the very best I can. And I'm generally

02:16.600 --> 02:27.720
satisfied that I've done the best that I can in that particular genre. They're
different thrusts, you might say. Right now, Anthony's fantasy commands a much

02:27.720 --> 02:39.940
larger audience than does his science fiction. For the decade or so that I wrote
science fiction, before I got into fantasy in any big way, I would have sales of

02:39.940 --> 02:51.160
50,000, 60,000 copies, 100,000. And some over the years, some of my better ones
would build up beyond that. I've only been into fantasy for the past five years.

02:52.060 --> 03:06.700
And they're already selling in the quarter million copies of class. I think my
first recent fantasy, A Spell for Chameleon, has now sold about 280,000 copies.

03:07.200 --> 03:16.140
So it's just much bigger than the science fiction, much faster and much more. We
asked Anthony what reason he gives for the popularity of fantasy in general

03:16.140 --> 03:26.720
these days. That's something that a lot of people are speculating on now. And my
answer may be fairly simple and others may not agree with it. For a number of

03:26.720 --> 03:37.120
years, there simply wasn't much market for fantasy. And everybody knew it, so
nobody wrote it. And Delray Books decided to take a plunge and get into fantasy

03:37.120 --> 03:48.120
in a big way. They went out and they tried to get good new authors. They tried
to get old ones to convert over and do serious, well-written fantasy. I was one

03:48.120 --> 03:57.120
of the ones that shifted over from science fiction to fantasy. And apparently it
worked, because now most of the best-selling fantasy is with this one publisher,

03:57.400 --> 04:08.820
Delray Books. And I conjecture that they took the plunge and it worked, that
when fantasy was given the same push that science fiction was, it had the same

04:08.820 --> 04:19.920
success and now is being carried on, perhaps on momentum, beyond the science
fiction levels. Now, most people will tell you there's a deep philosophical

04:19.920 --> 04:31.540
aspect that somehow people crave fantasy when they don't crave science fiction.
But I don't see that the world has changed that much in five years to make

04:31.540 --> 04:42.080
people suddenly crave a genre that they didn't want before. I think, again, the
answer has to be in the commercial aspect, in the push, in the advertising, in

04:42.080 --> 04:51.420
the promotion that they give the novels. I think people just didn't know about
fantasy before. But as I said, this is not an answer most people will give you.

04:51.420 --> 04:57.700
And I'm not sure whether it's accurate. It's just my theory. More with Piers
Anthony on our next show.

