06:31.480 --> 06:38.880
This is Daryl Lane. And Bill Vernon. Science fiction and fantasy author Piers
Anthony has written the enormously successful fantasy series, popularly called

06:38.880 --> 06:47.960
the Xanth series. A Spell for Chameleon appeared in September 1977. It tells the
story of Bink, a young man growing up in the enchanted land of Xanth, who is

06:47.960 --> 06:55.840
attempting to discover his unique individual magical ability. A Spell for
Chameleon sets the stage for the succeeding Xanth books. It is an adventure

06:55.840 --> 07:04.600
fantasy loaded with humor, especially puns. When A Spell for Chameleon appeared
in 1977, it was meant to be a standalone novel. However, as Anthony tells us, he

07:04.600 --> 07:14.300
came to write two sequels, The Source of Magic, which appeared in February 1979,
and Castle Rugna, which appeared in July of that year. No, it was no series. It

07:14.300 --> 07:26.820
was an individual novel that I did to try out a publisher and an editor. For all
I knew, it would be just one novel that would never repeat. But then it worked

07:26.820 --> 07:35.060
so well. I liked it, and the editor liked it. You see, this is a two-way street.
The author has to like doing something, but the editor also has to like his

07:35.060 --> 07:44.800
work. So before it was published, the editor said, Will you do another fantasy
for us? And he was not thinking of another in the same framework, and neither

07:44.800 --> 07:55.720
was I. But when I got to thinking about it and working out and trying to find
another fantasy setup, I realized that there was more that I wanted to say about

07:55.720 --> 08:04.640
The Land of Zanth. I sort of liked it. So I asked him if it would be all right
to do another one in that framework, and I think a little bit reluctantly. The

08:04.640 --> 08:14.080
editor agreed, and we did it. And then the thing was almost a bestseller. It did
very well, and that pretty well-established stance of the series, it just kept

08:14.080 --> 08:23.120
on going. We did a third one, said let's wrap it up as a trilogy and not do any
more. But then the readers started demanding more and more and more and more,

08:23.200 --> 08:33.680
and finally both the publisher and the author were... It's hard to say no when
the readers are begging for more, really. And so we have gone along, and it's

08:33.680 --> 08:42.400
been very rewarding, actually. So there's the answer. For those who say Piers
Anthony doesn't know how many books are in a trilogy, it wasn't his intent to

08:42.400 --> 08:50.580
make the Zanth series a trilogy. At this time, Centaur Isle, Ogre Ogre, and
Nightmare have been released, making a total of six in the series. Anthony told

08:50.580 --> 08:57.740
us that the series will probably go on indefinitely. At the time of the
interview, only four Zanth novels had been published. Well, I think of it as an

08:57.740 --> 09:10.140
open-ended series. I've actually written seven. I'm finishing the seventh one
now. I'm actually typing it right now. And I have two more that I'm thinking of.

09:10.800 --> 09:18.580
As you see, there are four in print, but there will be two more coming out later
this year, bringing it up to six. And then the seventh will appear about a year

09:18.580 --> 09:29.000
later. And I think as long as the market holds up, as long as there's demand,
I'll probably do one more Zanth novel a year, just indefinitely. When people get

09:29.000 --> 09:40.980
tired of Zanth and the sales go down, we'll quit. So it really has no end. I
suspect that it may go one novel a year for the next 20 years. I don't know. As

09:40.980 --> 09:49.280
the reader can well imagine, Anthony has a good time writing the Zanth novels. I
say it's not what I regard great literature. It's not terrifically challenging.

09:50.040 --> 09:59.960
But it has two things going for it. One is that it pays very well. And that's
all in a recession like this. It helps to have something you know will pay. And

09:59.960 --> 10:07.760
the other is that it is an awful lot of fun to do. I can just get there and sort
of relax. You know, it's like being at home with your shoes off and just

10:07.760 --> 10:19.320
relaxing and enjoying yourself. I enjoy it more than just about anything else.
But as I said, I like to do something with challenge so that I don't want to do

10:19.320 --> 10:30.600
nothing but Zanth. But in between other novels, it's very nice to come back and
just let myself go and work out puns, puns that nobody else would tolerate in

10:30.600 --> 10:38.960
Zanth. They're all right. And I probably enjoy writing them as much as my
readers enjoy reading them. More about Piers Anthony on our next show.

