12:17.300 --> 12:25.780
This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. Science fiction and fantasy author Piers
Anthony has over 40 novels to his credit. One of his best series is the Cluster

12:25.780 --> 12:34.240
Series, which Anthony calls Science Fantasy. It began as a designed trilogy
comprising Cluster, Chaining the Lady, and Curly and Quest, but two additional

12:34.240 --> 12:41.720
related novels have been added to the list, Thousand Star and Viscous Circle.
Central to this series of novels is the Tarot Religion, a much more

12:41.720 --> 12:48.220
sophisticated version of the Tarot fortune-telling cards, which have been around
hundreds of years. Anthony informed us that while he was researching the Cluster

12:48.220 --> 12:56.880
novels, he came across an interesting group who used Tarot cards. Here he tells
us how material he got from that group got included in the Cluster novels. I was

12:56.880 --> 13:06.100
doing the research. See, I work ahead. And so I was doing research and looking
at things and just studying things in general. I like to say now, I learn more

13:06.100 --> 13:17.880
each year than I ever did in school or college just because I like knowledge.
And so I was working on the Cluster novels at this time. And this material

13:18.840 --> 13:30.760
suddenly gave a new direction to it. So I put in Tarot scenes, one major scene,
one chapter in each of the Cluster novels. It had not originally been there. And

13:30.760 --> 13:45.220
I built, I merged the frameworks. Tarot is in the Cluster framework and the
Tarot material appears in the Cluster novels. It was a kind of amazing, you

13:45.220 --> 13:54.400
might say, of two ideas, the Tarot idea and the framework that I had already
developed for the Cluster novels. When the Cluster trilogy was completed,

13:54.740 --> 14:02.700
Anthony digressed to show the origin and original tenets of the Tarot religion.
The books making up this history are God of Tarot, Vision of Tarot, and Faith of

14:02.700 --> 14:10.840
Tarot. But be aware that this is not a trilogy, although some reviewers have
called it so. It is actually one long novel which was broken into three volumes,

14:11.120 --> 14:22.480
much to Anthony's displeasure. It was one quarter million word novel. I wrote it
in one piece. And a publisher balked at size. I don't know why. In mainstream,

14:22.820 --> 14:32.100
people can get quarter million word novels published and they're best sellers.
But in science fiction, they wouldn't do it for me. They insisted on breaking it

14:32.100 --> 14:45.660
up. Well, my agent and I fought this. We even went to the extent of taking about
a 30% cut in the payment for the sole reason to have it published as one novel.

14:46.240 --> 14:57.820
So they gave us the, I think they offered $15,000 and they cut it to $11,500 for
it and signed the agreement that they would publish it as one novel. Whereupon,

14:58.420 --> 15:09.300
they broke it up into three. They didn't give me back the money. And a publisher
published the first third of it and went out of business. That was Jove. Jove

15:09.300 --> 15:17.640
was brought out by the combine that, you know, Berkeley was part of. Berkeley
went ahead, published the other two novels in a different year so that I

15:17.640 --> 15:27.100
couldn't even get my novel published in one year. It bothered me because I feel
that this is the major novel of my career. Split into three parts and divided

15:27.100 --> 15:36.080
between two years. It washed me out totally. I had no chance to make a run for
any awards or anything like that. It was simply gone, which is what tends to

15:36.080 --> 15:48.720
happen to my more important work. So I'm rather put out about this because I
felt the major work of my career was virtually destroyed by the publisher. Not

15:48.720 --> 15:56.100
that the publisher set out to do that, but I mean by the publisher going out of
business right in the middle of my novel by refusing to honor the original

15:56.100 --> 16:03.660
commitment. Part of the agreement was when they finally broke it up, I had them
sign a paper saying, all right, if you've got to break it up, you've got to, but

16:03.660 --> 16:13.600
never will this be referred to as a trilogy because it's not. See, when I write
a novel, it's complete. I tie up the loose ends. And to publish a third of a

16:13.600 --> 16:21.340
novel and then call it a full novel in itself, that's just not the way I write.
Other people write that way. I'm aware of it. I don't. I like to wrap up my

16:21.340 --> 16:29.620
loose ends. As it happened, I saw a review of it, the first third. The reviewer
never even realized it was only a third of a novel. So apparently, he's used to

16:29.620 --> 16:33.900
seeing these fragments. More about Piers Anthony on our next show.

