23:48.780 --> 23:57.000
This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. The prolific science fiction and fantasy
author Piers Anthony is often outspoken, and once he was even blacklisted by the

23:57.000 --> 24:05.340
publishing community. Anthony is a man with strong principles. One of his
principles is that he responds to fan mail. It's a funny thing. I've never gone

24:05.340 --> 24:15.500
to a convention. I've never met people personally that way, mainly because I
don't like to travel and I do like to write. But I do answer my mail. Yesterday,

24:15.840 --> 24:25.680
I, yesterday, sorry. For last month, I simply went back and counted up the
letters I had written. It was 64 letters. I had to take off all weekends just to

24:25.680 --> 24:35.240
answer my fan mail. This is a problem. If it gets much worse, I'm going to have
to start slacking off on that because it takes me too long to finish a novel if

24:35.240 --> 24:47.280
I have to keep taking time off to answer the letters. But I am responsive. I do
read them. I think about them. Each is an individual letter relating to what the

24:47.280 --> 24:55.440
fan has told me, what his needs are. One reason Anthony feels so strongly about
responding to fan mail is that many of those who write him are children. You

24:55.440 --> 25:06.300
see, many of my letters are from children, 9, 10, 11, 12 years old. And I think
it's very important to them that I do answer them. When I was that age, I didn't

25:06.300 --> 25:19.980
like to be ignored when something was important to me. So I try to, it's the
golden rule, I try to treat them as I wish I had been treated. And I don't, you

25:19.980 --> 25:27.080
might say, well, what does a guy 10 years old have to tell me? Well, actually,
he can tell me how he feels, how he reacts, how important it is, and what

25:27.080 --> 25:36.480
influence my novelist had on him. He will do so with a lot more candor than an
adult will because he's not trying to impress me. He's just telling me what he

25:36.480 --> 25:47.220
likes. He doesn't have the art to be, you know, for duplicity. So that it's a
little like animal psychology. You can see the human motives in animals because

25:47.220 --> 25:55.940
the animals don't know enough to conceal them. So I value these letters. I
sometimes wish I just had more time, if I could have full time for writing and

25:55.940 --> 26:08.400
also full time for answering letters. So there is, it's been mostly this year,
considerable correspondence developing. And I would say 50 or 60 percent of it

26:08.400 --> 26:14.280
is by people under the age of, say, 18. It's mostly young readers that I get.

26:21.560 --> 26:28.060
Piers Anthony has a strong philosophical motive for writing. Making a living is
part of the motive, but it's not the whole thing, or even the most important

26:28.060 --> 26:39.380
part. I'd just like to think that I'm on Earth for some purpose other than just
to feed my face. I want to do something and try to leave the universe a better

26:39.380 --> 26:48.340
place than it was when I came into it. If there's anything in my power I can do
to improve things, then I want to do it. And I try to do this through the

26:48.340 --> 27:01.260
ability that I have, as a writer. And so I want to write, in the guise of
fiction, to write material that people will read and become better persons or

27:01.260 --> 27:09.520
get ideas that they wouldn't have. I've had some comments from fans saying that
after reading some of my novels, they're thinking of the Split Infinity series,

27:10.320 --> 27:18.440
they've decided that honesty is the best policy. Now they admire honesty. Well,
that pleases me. That's the kind of thing I want to do. If a person was planning

27:18.440 --> 27:27.540
to be dishonest and he reads one of my novels and then he decides that he really
would rather be honest, I believe in honesty. I want to encourage it. I think

27:27.540 --> 27:38.260
there should be more of it in the world. So I am trying to have a beneficial
effect, you might say, to justify my own existence. I'm making money at it, yes.

27:38.460 --> 27:47.400
But while I'm making the money, I also want to do something that, well, when I
die, I can look back and say, I have done something useful in the world. So this

27:47.400 --> 27:57.200
is why I'm not satisfied just to write and get paid for it and not to worry
about the theme or the content. I want to do something that I can be satisfied

27:57.200 --> 28:00.160
with, that I can be proud of, and that will help people.

